@*Movie - Exit 8 | Genre - Horror / Psychological | Thoughts - Having been based on an indie game with no dialogue or story, Exit 8 needed to add a lot of extra details to justify its runtime. 
These extra details could have ended up feeling disjointed or unnecessary, but instead they were woven together in a way thatdoes not interfere with the spirit of the original game or the tone of the movie.
The movie is not scaryso much as it is unsettling, but it still makes for an interesting watch. | 
Real Facts - None of the characters in Exit 8 have names, and the movie's credits simply list them with titles, such as Lost Man for the main character
*@
@*Movie - Iron Lung | Genre - Horror / Sci-Fi | Thoughts - Iron Lung is a horror film that relies heavily on atmosphere and tension to create its unsettling effect. The movie's pacing is deliberate, allowing the audience to build up dread before the inevitable scares. 
It also does not heavily rely on jump scares like many other horror titles. While it may lack the polish of bigger-budget films, it succeeds in creating a genuinely creepy experience. | 
Real Facts - Iron Lung makes use of 80000 gallons of fake blood, the most used in any horror title to date. *@
@*Movie - GOAT | Genre - Sports | Thoughts - While similar to Zootopia in setting, GOAT starts off in what could be called the slums of Zootopia and follows Will Harris, a young (anthropomorphic) goat who dreams of joining his favorite roarball team, the Thorns. 
He finally gets his chance when his initial trouncing of a top player goes viral and gains the attention of the team's owner. GOAT's story could be considered formulaic and predictable, but the story is done so well and with such passion that it hardly matters.
Real facts - Lenny Williamson, a giraffe, is voiced by Stephen Curry, a famously short basketball player *@
@*Movie - Hoppers | Genre - Adventure | Thoughts - Hoppers starts off by revealing a heavy emotional core for the film, but the tone of most of the movie does not match it. Furthermore, the film's third act, while entertaining and zany, does not match the rest of the film's tone and is not for everyone.
    Real facts - All beaver noises (from the human's erspective) were done by the movie's director, Daniel Chong.)*@
@*Movie - The Super Mario Bros Movie | Genre - Fantasy / Adventure | Thoughts - As gorgeous as the animation is, like everything Illumination has made, The Super Mario Bros Movie suffers from a lack of cohesion between scenes. As a result, the film feels more like a compilation of fun cutscenes than a proper narrative
